- Good.

516
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:17,871
Irene really likes the girls.

517
00:43:18,040 --> 00:43:19,871
Always has.

518
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:23,634
It's too bad she couldn't
take Cuddles, huh?

519
00:43:23,840 --> 00:43:25,273
That might not be a problem.

520
00:43:25,480 --> 00:43:27,198
Really?

521
00:43:27,360 --> 00:43:29,157
She suggested I move in with her.

522
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:30,509
What?

523
00:43:30,680 --> 00:43:33,274
- You wanna move?
- No. I--

524
00:43:33,920 --> 00:43:35,911
I love living here with you.

525
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:40,719
I'd still technically be living here, so
you wouldn't need another roommate.

526
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:42,274
Her place is huge.

527
00:43:42,480 --> 00:43:45,040
It's not like you couldn't use
the extra closet space.

528
00:43:45,200 --> 00:43:48,033
I don't want more space, I want....

529
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:54,354
It's just something to think about.

530
00:43:55,400 --> 00:43:57,391
Nothing's set in stone.

531
00:43:58,200 --> 00:44:00,873
Plus, we'd be able to keep Cuddles.

532
00:44:01,680 --> 00:44:04,831
Yeah, well, I was thinking maybe
I'd stay here for Thanksgiving...

533
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:07,230
...and see you guys at Christmas.

534
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:09,709
You know what, Mom?
I'm really swamped right now.

535
00:44:09,880 --> 00:44:13,395
Could I call you guys back?
Okay. Bye.

536
00:44:45,720 --> 00:44:48,109
Feel how nice and warm
it is in there?

537
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:56,874
Oh, my God. What's wrong?

538
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:01,438
- Cuddles got out.
- What?

539
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:04,558
I took her with me to do laundry
and she was in the basket...

540
00:45:04,760 --> 00:45:07,638
...and she ran off.
And I went after her but....

541
00:45:07,800 --> 00:45:08,915
I'm sorry.

542
00:45:11,920 --> 00:45:13,638
I'm gonna go find her.

543
00:45:20,920 --> 00:45:24,629
Maybe it's karma. We weren't allowed
to keep her anyway.

544
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:29,160
- It's all my fault.
- It was an accident.

545
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:31,595
It's just stress after stress,
you know?

546
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:36,153
Is there something else wrong?

547
00:45:40,160 --> 00:45:42,833
My parents really want me
to come home for Thanksgiving.

548
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:44,149
And you don't wanna go?

549
00:45:44,640 --> 00:45:46,915
Emily died two days
before Thanksgiving.

550
00:45:48,160 --> 00:45:52,119
It hasn't always been the most festive
holiday in the Matthews household.

551
00:45:52,280 --> 00:45:54,794
I know I should be there,
but, I don't know...

552
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:58,157
...it's like there's a ghost
at the table, you know?

553
00:46:00,280 --> 00:46:01,713
So....

554
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:05,149
You can come with me.

555
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:08,831
Spend Thanksgiving at my house.

556
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:11,679
- Your folks wouldn't mind?
- Please.

557
00:46:11,840 --> 00:46:14,229
Stephen also asked me to stay...

558
00:46:14,440 --> 00:46:16,670
...but thank you.

559
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:19,349
Midterm designs are due Friday.

560
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:22,999
Now, remember, people: simplicity.

561
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:25,515
Who is the founder of our industry?

562
00:46:26,360 --> 00:46:29,318
Eve. When she handed Adam
the fig leaf.

563
00:46:30,720 --> 00:46:32,551
Have a good day.

564
00:46:35,320 --> 00:46:36,992
- Sara.
- Yeah?

565
00:46:37,520 --> 00:46:40,193
- Can I see you in my office?
- Sure.

566
00:46:41,040 --> 00:46:45,352
I love the danger in your work.
It's kinky and edgy.

567
00:46:45,560 --> 00:46:48,870
I love the fact that there's all these,
like, dark recesses in this...

568
00:46:49,040 --> 00:46:52,396
...innocent exterior. The juxtaposition
is awesome. That's great.

569
00:46:52,560 --> 00:46:54,551
- Thank you.
- And I mean, styles, you know--

570
00:46:54,720 --> 00:46:57,757
They change so rapidly
in the fashion world.

571
00:46:58,040 --> 00:47:01,749
Because you got your particular cut,
your technique, you know, the--

572
00:47:02,040 --> 00:47:04,270
Which is what makes it
so amazing and exciting.

573
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:08,195
Exactly. Which is why I go
to fashion week every year in Paris.

574
00:47:08,920 --> 00:47:12,754
To catch up on what's fresh
and amazing and.... What else?

575
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:14,558
- Exciting.
- Exciting.

576
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:17,234
- And, let's face it, to go to the parties.
- Sure.

577
00:47:17,400 --> 00:47:21,029
The budget allows for me
to bring an assistant every year.

578
00:47:21,240 --> 00:47:24,596
Usually it's a senior, but not always.

579
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:27,753
There's a lot of talent in this class...

580
00:47:27,920 --> 00:47:32,596
...but the best designers push
the boundaries on what's acceptable.

581
00:47:34,280 --> 00:47:35,315
They take chances.

582
00:47:45,520 --> 00:47:47,238
I should go.

583
00:47:47,400 --> 00:47:49,277
All right. Well, good meeting.

584
00:47:50,520 --> 00:47:53,239
The offer still stands, Sara.

585
00:47:53,440 --> 00:47:54,589
Chance of a lifetime.

586
00:48:03,080 --> 00:48:05,640
- What's wrong?
- My design professor just kissed me.

587
00:48:06,960 --> 00:48:10,475
- Are you all right?
- And I think the asshole's married.

588
00:48:13,440 --> 00:48:16,830
- Are you gonna tell Stephen?
- No, that'll just cause problems.

589
00:48:20,200 --> 00:48:22,077
I'm here for you.

590
00:48:22,320 --> 00:48:25,118
- I know.
- Thank you for telling me.

591
00:48:28,600 --> 00:48:31,433
- What can I do?
- Nothing.

592
00:48:41,720 --> 00:48:43,870
- Professor Roberts?
- That's right.

593
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:45,877
I'm glad you're still here.

594
00:48:46,080 --> 00:48:48,799
Yeah, well, I was just leaving.

595
00:48:50,880 --> 00:48:54,236
- You're not a student of mine.
- No, not yet.

596
00:48:55,240 --> 00:48:57,151
That's why I'm here.

597
00:48:57,840 --> 00:49:00,308
- I'm failing Intro Psych.
- Yeah, and why is that?

598
00:49:01,680 --> 00:49:02,829
I'm bored.

599
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:06,635
Well, I'm real sorry about that,
but I don't know what I can do to help.

600
00:49:06,880 --> 00:49:10,190
Tomorrow is the last day
to drop a course.

601
00:49:10,360 --> 00:49:14,911
If I don't add another one in its place,
then I'll fall way behind in credits.

602
00:49:15,360 --> 00:49:18,397
Daddy won't take that very well.

603
00:49:19,040 --> 00:49:20,712
He might even pull the plug...

604
00:49:22,120 --> 00:49:24,873
...which means I'm pretty much
at your mercy.

605
00:49:27,520 --> 00:49:28,839
Look, I really don't take--

606
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:32,549
It's not my policy to take on students
in the middle of the term.

607
00:49:32,720 --> 00:49:34,756
Do I look like
just any student to you?

608
00:49:38,520 --> 00:49:41,830
- Oh, your wife's very pretty.
- Oh, it's my ex-wife.

609
00:49:43,400 --> 00:49:46,631
I might have to ask you
a few questions first.

610
00:49:47,440 --> 00:49:49,715
- Ask me anything.
- You have design experience?

611
00:49:50,160 --> 00:49:54,153
- None.
- What do you know about clothes?

612
00:49:56,240 --> 00:49:58,356
Only one thing.

613
00:49:58,560 --> 00:49:59,879
Yeah, and what's that?

614
00:50:01,760 --> 00:50:04,752
I look better out of them
than in them.

615
00:50:06,080 --> 00:50:08,469
Well, I think we can work
something out.

616
00:50:09,240 --> 00:50:12,630
- Just tell me and I'll do anything.
- Kiss me.

617
00:50:12,800 --> 00:50:16,918
- What?
- I said kiss me.

618
00:50:25,200 --> 00:50:27,395
Professor Roberts,
you're hurting me.

619
00:50:35,960 --> 00:50:38,394
Oh, you little tease.

620
00:50:42,480 --> 00:50:44,994
Get off of me! Stop it! Stop!

621
00:50:45,200 --> 00:50:46,269
- Quiet!
- No!

622
00:50:46,480 --> 00:50:49,438
- Shut up! Quiet!
- Get off of me! Stop! Leave me alone!

623
00:50:49,600 --> 00:50:52,114
- You're hurting me!
- Quiet. Shut up, would you?

624
00:50:52,360 --> 00:50:55,079
- No! I said no!
- Shut up, you little bitch tease!

625
00:50:55,280 --> 00:50:57,430
Sylvester, stop it! No!

626
00:50:57,640 --> 00:51:00,632
- Quiet! Quiet!
- Get off of me! No! I said no!

627
00:51:01,240 --> 00:51:02,958
- What--?
- Stop!

628
00:51:06,440 --> 00:51:09,955
- Just tell me and I'll do anything.
- Kiss me.

629
00:51:10,120 --> 00:51:14,432
- What?
- I said kiss me.

630
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:17,714
What do you want?

631
00:51:17,880 --> 00:51:20,678
- Professor Roberts, you're hurting me.
- Give me that!

632
00:51:23,320 --> 00:51:26,039
You don't have to do this.
You don't have to do this.

633
00:51:26,280 --> 00:51:28,111
What do you want? Okay, come on.

634
00:51:28,800 --> 00:51:33,271
- I'll pay for it. All right, I'll pay for that.
- Yes, you will.

635
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:41,797
Come on in.

636
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:44,991
Come on in. Hello.

637
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:48,552
Just take your seats, please.
Welcome.

638
00:51:48,760 --> 00:51:51,558
I'm Professor Jacobs
and I'll be taking over the class...

639
00:51:51,760 --> 00:51:53,318
...for the rest of the semester.

640
00:51:53,800 --> 00:51:54,869
What happened?

641
00:51:55,040 --> 00:51:57,508
They're calling it a leave of absence,
but I heard...

642
00:51:57,680 --> 00:52:00,877
...someone sent the dean a recording
of him hitting on a student.

643
00:52:01,040 --> 00:52:03,713
- Oh, my God.
- Yeah, I know.

644
00:52:03,880 --> 00:52:05,029
I know.

645
00:52:05,280 --> 00:52:07,350
Well, that's what you call
instant karma.

646
00:52:42,080 --> 00:52:44,719
- Bye, Sara.
- Bye, Jake.

647
00:52:45,920 --> 00:52:48,354
Okay, I have made a decision.

648
00:52:48,760 --> 00:52:50,352
- You ready?
- Yeah, let's hear it.

649
00:52:50,920 --> 00:52:52,558
All right.

650
00:52:52,960 --> 00:52:54,791
- I'm gonna quit the band.
- What? Why?

651
00:52:54,960 --> 00:52:57,758
It's a huge waste of time
and we suck.

652
00:52:57,960 --> 00:52:59,791
I disagree,
but why would you say that?

653
00:52:59,960 --> 00:53:01,916
All right, let me think about this.

654
00:53:03,400 --> 00:53:05,470
The only places
that we can get booked...

655
00:53:05,640 --> 00:53:09,235
...are my frat house
and my girlfriend's coffee shop.

656
00:53:09,400 --> 00:53:10,435
That's not good.

657
00:53:10,600 --> 00:53:14,115
- Did you just say "my girlfriend"?
- Oh, you heard me.

658
00:53:19,120 --> 00:53:22,078
So do you think it'd be fun
to stay here for Thanksgiving?

659
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:25,596
Yeah, you know, you got dinner
at the frat house, football games...

660
00:53:25,800 --> 00:53:28,951
...and the always awkward
homoerotic humor.

661
00:53:29,120 --> 00:53:32,430
- That sounds like a blast. It's fun times.
- Oh, yeah. It's very good.

662
00:53:32,640 --> 00:53:34,949
A little awkward at times, but....

663
00:54:45,240 --> 00:54:48,198
Rebecca. Oh, my God.
What happened?

664
00:54:48,360 --> 00:54:52,478
- What happened?
- I was looking for Cuddles.

665
00:54:53,560 --> 00:54:57,553
A man pulled me into an alley.
And he--

666
00:54:57,720 --> 00:54:58,914
Okay.

667
00:54:59,080 --> 00:55:01,435
- I got away, though.
- Okay.

668
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:03,192
Okay.

669
00:55:08,600 --> 00:55:09,715
Oh, my God.

670
00:55:11,520 --> 00:55:14,080
It's not deep, thank God.

671
00:55:14,240 --> 00:55:16,117
You should see a doctor.

672
00:55:16,400 --> 00:55:18,595
- No.
- Rebecca, you need to.

673
00:55:18,760 --> 00:55:21,399
- And then the police.
- No, I can't.

674
00:55:21,600 --> 00:55:24,353
You're calling or I am.
There is a psycho walking around.

675
00:55:24,520 --> 00:55:27,080
- Please, I didn't even see him.
- It doesn't matter.

676
00:55:27,240 --> 00:55:30,710
- You still need to talk to the police.
- Please. I only want you to know.

677
00:55:30,880 --> 00:55:33,599
- Rebecca.
- Don't tell anybody, please.

678
00:55:33,760 --> 00:55:36,228
Okay, I won't tell them.

679
00:55:40,640 --> 00:55:43,074
- Just let me help you.
- Are you mad at me?

680
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:46,758
Why would I be mad at you?

681
00:55:49,240 --> 00:55:52,949
Sorry again about not staying,
but Rebecca....

682
00:55:53,160 --> 00:55:54,752
No, I get it. I get it.

683
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:59,073
I'm just gonna make out with my pillow
and pretend it's you anyway, so....

684
00:55:59,720 --> 00:56:01,153
Just say you're gonna miss me.

685
00:56:02,280 --> 00:56:03,315
I will miss you.

686
00:56:05,080 --> 00:56:07,036
I'll miss you too.

687
00:56:15,640 --> 00:56:19,269
You know, I haven't heard from Jason
in weeks.

688
00:56:19,960 --> 00:56:21,632
It's weird how he stopped calling.

689
00:56:22,080 --> 00:56:23,832
That's what you wanted, right?

690
00:56:25,640 --> 00:56:26,959
Yeah.

691
00:56:27,800 --> 00:56:29,950
Yeah, I guess it is.

692
00:56:38,320 --> 00:56:39,753
This is your home?

693
00:56:39,920 --> 00:56:43,629
This is my parents' house.
It was never a home when I lived here.

694
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:01,150
Hello?

695
00:57:01,640 --> 00:57:03,790
Is anybody here?

696
00:57:07,160 --> 00:57:09,515
Hi, Rebecca.

697
00:57:10,120 --> 00:57:11,838
- Hi.
- Hi, honey.

698
00:57:12,080 --> 00:57:14,514
- Oh, my God. What happened?
- Mom, stop. Nothing.

699
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:17,399
- What do you mean? It's not nothing.
- Leave it alone.

700
00:57:19,720 --> 00:57:21,358
We didn't think you'd make it.

701
00:57:21,600 --> 00:57:23,397
Why wouldn't I?

702
00:57:25,640 --> 00:57:27,915
And you are?

703
00:57:28,880 --> 00:57:29,915
I'm Sara.

704
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:32,515
- Sara's my roommate.
- Hi, I'm Jeff.

705
00:57:32,680 --> 00:57:36,195
- Nice to meet you.
- Hi. Welcome. I'm Alison.

706
00:57:36,400 --> 00:57:38,038
Thanks.

707
00:57:38,360 --> 00:57:40,191
Come on, let me show you my room.

708
00:57:46,400 --> 00:57:48,834
You didn't tell them
we were coming?

709
00:57:49,240 --> 00:57:51,708
They didn't need to know.

710
00:57:58,040 --> 00:58:00,634
- Nice room.
- I guess.

711
00:58:07,080 --> 00:58:09,913
- Who is she?
- That's just some high-school work.

712
00:58:11,400 --> 00:58:13,755
I haven't gotten around
to taking it down yet.

713
00:58:14,040 --> 00:58:17,237
Sara, I hope you're not a vegetarian.

714
00:58:17,440 --> 00:58:19,237
Oh, no, not at all.

715
00:58:25,800 --> 00:58:29,236
- Rebecca's an awesome roommate.
- That's nice to hear.

716
00:58:29,440 --> 00:58:33,319
I'm sure she likes you, because she's
never brought anyone home before.

717
00:58:33,560 --> 00:58:35,391
- Dad.
- What?

718
00:58:35,560 --> 00:58:37,596
As a parent, you worry.

719
00:58:37,760 --> 00:58:41,548
You protect your daughter all her life
and then she goes off to college.

720
00:58:41,760 --> 00:58:45,230
And she's on her own. And you
never know who she'll be exposed to.

721
00:58:45,400 --> 00:58:46,719
Dad.

722
00:58:49,760 --> 00:58:52,593
Sara, we're going to make up
a very nice room for you.

723
00:58:52,760 --> 00:58:54,432
No, she'll stay with me.

724
00:58:54,600 --> 00:58:56,591
- Right?
- Okay.

725
00:58:57,240 --> 00:58:59,117
Wonderful.

726
00:59:10,640 --> 00:59:12,073
Dad.

727
00:59:12,720 --> 00:59:15,712
Bec. You scared me.

728
00:59:17,120 --> 00:59:18,712
Why are you up so late?

729
00:59:31,800 --> 00:59:34,633
- So how you doing?
- I'm fine.

730
00:59:36,120 --> 00:59:38,270
My grades are good.

731
00:59:39,520 --> 00:59:41,158
That's not what I meant.

732
00:59:41,320 --> 00:59:43,151
I'm making friends.

733
00:59:45,320 --> 00:59:47,993
Rebecca, look at me for a second.

734
00:59:53,400 --> 00:59:55,311
Your mother and I
are very fond of you.

735
00:59:55,480 --> 00:59:57,277
I know.

736
01:00:00,200 --> 01:00:01,997
All right,
I'm gonna head on up to bed.

737
01:00:10,680 --> 01:00:12,159
Hi.

738
01:00:13,080 --> 01:00:14,195
What are you up to?

739
01:00:14,360 --> 01:00:16,669
Rebecca's gonna show me
her high-school hangouts.

740
01:00:16,880 --> 01:00:19,030
- Wonderful.
- Yeah.

741
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:22,033
- Rebecca's doing really well.
- She's doing good.

742
01:00:22,800 --> 01:00:24,153
She's taking her medication?

743
01:00:26,280 --> 01:00:28,157
Medication?

744
01:00:29,560 --> 01:00:32,279
Well, you girls have
a wonderful time.

745
01:00:34,400 --> 01:00:36,038
Come on.

746
01:00:45,040 --> 01:00:47,190
Is everything okay?

747
01:00:48,360 --> 01:00:49,918
Yeah.

748
01:00:50,720 --> 01:00:52,597
It's just....

749
01:00:53,720 --> 01:00:56,598
It's nice to see
where you come from.

750
01:00:59,240 --> 01:01:00,309
Come on.

751
01:01:03,120 --> 01:01:06,749
- This is the best.
- Smells really good.

752
01:01:07,240 --> 01:01:09,356
I used to come here, like, every day.

753
01:01:13,440 --> 01:01:16,079
- It's Rebecca.
- Well, just stay out here.

754
01:01:23,880 --> 01:01:25,598
Do you know them?

755
01:01:26,360 --> 01:01:28,430
That'll be 5.57.

756
01:01:36,080 --> 01:01:38,594
That's the girl from your drawings.

757
01:01:40,880 --> 01:01:42,279
Rebecca?

758
01:01:43,280 --> 01:01:44,429
Let's leave.

759
01:01:51,360 --> 01:01:53,237
Hi, Maria.

760
01:01:55,000 --> 01:01:56,115
Hi.

761
01:01:56,280 --> 01:01:58,111
I wanted to introduce you to Sara.

762
01:01:59,640 --> 01:02:01,437
My roommate.

763
01:02:02,280 --> 01:02:05,431
- Hi.
- Hey.

764
01:02:13,120 --> 01:02:15,111
Maybe we should go.

765
01:02:19,680 --> 01:02:21,159
Rebecca.

766
01:02:26,920 --> 01:02:28,717
We were never friends.

767
01:02:34,160 --> 01:02:36,276
Come on, let's go.

768
01:02:58,320 --> 01:03:01,198
Oh, good, Irene's back in town.

769
01:03:18,480 --> 01:03:20,675
- Good run?
- Great.

770
01:03:21,600 --> 01:03:23,431
I'm going to the studio.

771
01:03:23,600 --> 01:03:25,192
All right, I'll catch you later.

772
01:03:25,400 --> 01:03:28,597
Don't wait up. I feel inspired.

773
01:03:40,560 --> 01:03:42,710
